Not sure what would be the use case for this but I would go by overriding the LoginView

```
class TokenLimitingLoginView(LoginView):
    max_token_count_per_user = 10
    def post(self, request, format=None):
        user_token_count = request.user.auth_token_set.all().count()
        if user_token_count >= self.max_token_count_per_user:
            return Response(
                {'error': 'User has reached max number of token per user'},
                status=status.HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED
            )
        super().post(request, format)
```

