I'm not sure it's a good idea to test exceptions in YAML tests like (`ValueError` or `TypeError`), except for OpenFisca-level exceptions (`ParameterNotFound` for example).

`nosetests` uses [`assert_raises`](https://docs.python.org/2.7/library/unittest.html#unittest.TestCase.assertRaises) from Python unittest, but this function is not available in the YAML formalism.

